Environment Variables

echo means Printing on the screen.
$ means variable or in wildcard it means end.

command:  env ( show environment variables)
Path variable: echo $PATH

to run any script
1. bash <script name>
2. . <script name>


For each user there are two files for login 
if shell is bash
  1. .bashrc
  3. .bash_profile
  
  these files are executed when user logs in and can be executed manually also.
  
  
  
  #############################################################################
  
  commands
  
  installation in linux
  
  ubuntu: 
  
      apt-get install <software name>
      
  redhat:
          rpm install <software name>
          
  #man <command name> for help
   
    
   
   for copy
   
   cp <source file> <destination file>
   cp -r <source directory> <destionation directory>
   
   for move
   
   mv <source file/directory> <destination file/directory>
   
   
      

  
 
